96
00:08:17,300 --> 00:08:19,100
Have it say,

97
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:24,200
"Butchie. Woe to them
that call evil good, and good evil."

98
00:08:25,500 --> 00:08:30,900
Sign it, "Your true and loyal friend,
Proposition Joe."

99
00:08:34,300 --> 00:08:38,600
You ain't thinking no kindly note
gonna slow Omar coming at us.

100
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:42,200
It's how I feel.
He was a good man.

101
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:44,800
- And Marlo?
- Marlo is Marlo, man.

102
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:47,500
He weren't the one that
put me in this trick bag.

103
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:51,700
The motherfucker who snuggled up
and whispered in Marlo's ear did that.

104
00:08:51,700 --> 00:08:55,600
I know what you thinking,
and I ain't making a move against no kin,

105
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:58,200
not till I got more to go on than words.

106
00:08:58,300 --> 00:09:00,800
And knowing my sister's son the way I do,

107
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:03,300
if the boy got 50 grand in his pocket,

108
00:09:03,300 --> 00:09:07,800
it ain't gonna be long before it jump out
and find itself in some salesman hand.

109
00:09:07,900 --> 00:09:10,000
And that kind of goody, we know.

110
00:09:11,100 --> 00:09:14,400
In the meantime, if Omar coming
for any of us, he coming for me.

111
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:16,700
And out of respect
for that man's skill set,

112
00:09:16,700 --> 00:09:20,100
I'm gonna take myself out of the lineup
after the meet tomorrow.

113
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:25,600
Till this shit sort itself out,
Cheese gonna watch the shop.

114
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:27,200
You gonna watch Cheese.

115
00:09:32,300 --> 00:09:34,800
Very clean. Very nice.

116
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:42,100
But, this is unnecessary.

117
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:44,900
It was not our intent to mislead.

118
00:09:44,900 --> 00:09:48,500
When I spoke before,
about the condition of your money,

119
00:09:48,500 --> 00:09:52,000
I was talking... in symbols.

120
00:09:52,100 --> 00:09:53,900
The money, it came from the street,

121
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:58,200
and so I thought you came...
from the street.

122
00:09:58,800 --> 00:10:01,300
I did.

123
00:10:01,300 --> 00:10:02,300
I do.

124
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:06,900
It was not the money that concerned me.
You have been more than generous,

125
00:10:06,900 --> 00:10:10,500
and this is a gift
of an honorable man, clearly.

126
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:12,600
But, in accepting such a gift,

127
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:16,100
we would give you
the wrong impression.

128
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:26,100
You come from the street?

129
00:10:27,300 --> 00:10:30,400
The street... doesn't concern us.

130
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:33,300
We know a man here,
and we trust him.

131
00:10:33,300 --> 00:10:38,800
But... to know more people,
to learn more names,

132
00:10:38,900 --> 00:10:41,400
to have them learn our names...

133
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:43,800
I'm not here to badmouth Prop Joe

134
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:46,100
but people depend on me.

135
00:10:46,100 --> 00:10:48,400
Now, last year, there was a robbery.

136
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:53,400
I'm saying, you know,
what if this happens again?

137
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:56,600
- Where do that put my people?
- That's for you to discuss with Joe.

138
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:59,500
All I'm asking for
is an insurance policy.

139
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:02,400
You know, something covers me
and covers you.

140
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:04,300
And covers Joe.

141
00:11:11,300 --> 00:11:15,000
The young man makes a point.

142
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:18,600
You're right.
These are volatile times.

143
00:11:18,600 --> 00:11:21,800
It is not unreasonable
to carry insurance.

144
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:25,600
Who can say what tomorrow will show us?

145
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:29,400
You go.

146
00:11:29,500 --> 00:11:31,100
Be safe.

147
00:11:34,900 --> 00:11:37,300
Your case.

148
00:11:37,300 --> 00:11:41,200
Oh, y'all came a ways.
Put it to expenses.

149
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:51,700
If we were to tell him no,
he will still come back.

150
00:11:51,700 --> 00:11:54,000
This he shows us.

151
00:11:57,100 --> 00:11:58,900
But he is not Joe.

152
00:12:00,700 --> 00:12:02,400
He is not Joe.

153
00:12:04,700 --> 00:12:08,800
If I follow this, the senator's mother-in-law
gave him $80,000

154
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:11,800
that he used as a down payment
on some property.

155
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:14,500
Later, he paid the money back,
which makes it a loan.

156
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:16,600
Which falsifies the loan application.

157
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:19,300
The moment he signs the application,
he's exposed.

158
00:12:19,300 --> 00:12:23,500
Title 18 of the US Code,
chapter 47, section 10-14,

159
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:28,400
Loan And Credit Applications.
30 years and not to exceed $1 million.

160
00:12:28,400 --> 00:12:31,400
The US Attorney's office,
call it "the head shot."

161
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:35,300
30 years for something that every college kid
does with a starter home.

162
00:12:35,300 --> 00:12:37,200
Daddy loans you money to qualify;

163
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:41,200
a couple years later, you pay him back.
30 years.

164
00:12:41,300 --> 00:12:45,800
With leverage like that,
this case needs to go federal.

165
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:55,800
Outstanding work, Detective.

166
00:12:55,800 --> 00:12:58,100
Let me have some time to digest this.

167
00:13:00,100 --> 00:13:02,500
Counselor, a moment?

168
00:13:06,900 --> 00:13:10,300
Is there another way to go at this?
How strong are our theft counts?

169
00:13:10,300 --> 00:13:15,100
Straightforward document cases, four counts.
He stole from his own charities.

170
00:13:15,100 --> 00:13:17,800
We convict, that's ten years per count.

171
00:13:17,900 --> 00:13:21,600
Nothing to sneeze at,
even without the bank charge.

172
00:13:47,100 --> 00:13:50,700
You think it might be OK for me
to sit in on one of your budget meetings?

173
00:13:50,700 --> 00:13:51,900
On our good days.

174
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,800
Ed? This is Scott Templeton.

175
00:13:56,900 --> 00:14:00,200
Scott, good to meet you. Have a seat.

176
00:14:00,300 --> 00:14:01,700
Give me a sec.

177
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:09,200
Next mouth needs fed
is the Right Reverend Isaac Cason.

178
00:14:09,300 --> 00:14:12,700
Christ! All's I'm trying to do is dump Burrell.

179
00:14:12,700 --> 00:14:16,100
You want us to swallow Rawls,
you'd better grease that morsel up good.

180
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:21,400
Rawls for 6 months, then Daniels.
What, Daniels isn't black enough for you guys?

181
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:26,000
They don't know him. They know Burrell,
and they could phone when they needed.

182
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:28,800
Burrell came in here with bad stats.
He lied to my face.

183
00:14:28,900 --> 00:14:31,400
Rawls lied, too,
but you're making him acting commissioner.

184
00:14:31,500 --> 00:14:35,400
Only till Daniels gets groomed.
We can't fire everyone all at once.

185
00:14:35,400 --> 00:14:38,400
- This isn't getting us anywhere.
- Only two more left.

186
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:41,600
Fine. How can I be of assistance
to the good Reverend Cason?

187
00:14:41,700 --> 00:14:45,000
He has property he wants
to convert to senior housing.

188
00:14:45,100 --> 00:14:46,200
Can we accommodate him?

189
00:14:46,200 --> 00:14:49,800
We're broke, but we could steer
some Hud money his way.

190
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:52,500
That leaves Reverend Myrtle Smith.

191
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:55,900
She wants to extend parking
to a vacant lot next to her church.

192
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:57,900
- It's city property.
- That's it?

193
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:01,800
- The last is the least.
- A long-term lease, dollar a year.

194
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:08,100
Then there's the matter
of Mcculloh Homes.

195
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:12,900
The same Mcculloh Homes that's adjacent to
Andy Krawczyk's $300 million expansion

196
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:15,700
- Of the state office complex.
- Over 500 units.

197
00:15:15,800 --> 00:15:18,700
Public housing.
You'll need that Hope VI money for that.

198
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:21,300
- Is there any Hope VI money?
- It doesn't matter.

199
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:24,800
All madam president wants
from us is the green light.

200
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:26,900
You want him gone, right?

201
00:15:30,700 --> 00:15:31,900
It's good stuff.

202
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:34,500
Some of your feature work
is a little wrought

203
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:38,100
for what we do here language-wise,
but it all shows initiative.

204
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:40,100
That's the style they want from me

205
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:43,500
but to tell you the truth,
I prefer to write it dry.

206
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:46,000
- You've been in Baltimore long?
- Two years.

207
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:49,800
Before that, I was at
the Kansas City Star for three years,

208
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:51,600
Wichita Eagle before that.

209
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:55,400
- The Sun's a fine paper.
- Before the cutbacks, maybe.

210
00:15:55,400 --> 00:15:57,900
Well, they still beat us
often enough in Annapolis

211
00:15:57,900 --> 00:16:01,100
for my Maryland desk
to take them seriously.

212
00:16:01,100 --> 00:16:05,000
You have anything to do with
those ground rent stories last year?

213
00:16:05,100 --> 00:16:07,600
It's good stuff, real good stuff.

214
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:20,300
You wanted to go to
the page one meeting, right?

215
00:16:20,300 --> 00:16:22,000
Another time, maybe.

216
00:16:25,900 --> 00:16:28,500
Anyway, as he says,
we'll keep the résumé on file.

217
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:32,600
A few more clips, a little more seasoning,
we'll take another look, OK?

218
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:35,700
You can just toss that.

219
00:16:44,100 --> 00:16:45,300
That's the plan -

220
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:47,900
let him cut his teeth
as deputy for operations,

221
00:16:47,900 --> 00:16:50,900
and in six months, make him.

222
00:16:50,900 --> 00:16:54,800
He's not the spic-and-span boy
they think he is.

223
00:16:58,500 --> 00:17:02,300
He came up in the eastern district,
part of a bad drug unit

224
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:05,200
that was skimming seized drug money.
I had the feds...

225
00:17:05,300 --> 00:17:09,000
This isn't about Daniels.
You came in with bad stats.

226
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:10,900
For the mayor, that was the last straw.

227
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:15,100
My numbers were clean, they had gone
through staff review. You tell Carcetti...

228
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:16,800
Ervin, it doesn't matter now.

229
00:17:16,900 --> 00:17:19,700
You're done. Carcetti has moved on you.

230
00:17:21,600 --> 00:17:25,800
You tell him if he does me like this,
I'll do Daniels.

231
00:17:25,800 --> 00:17:29,700
Kill Daniels, and we end up with Bill Rawls
as police commissioner.

232
00:17:29,700 --> 00:17:34,100
The ministers, the caucus, the council -
they'll live with Daniels. Why?

233
00:17:34,100 --> 00:17:37,500
Because Carcetti gave away
the store just to push you out.

234
00:17:37,600 --> 00:17:39,700
30 pieces of silver each, huh?

235
00:17:39,700 --> 00:17:43,000
We'll have your back. I promise you.

236
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:47,900
Full pension and a job on the mayor's
criminal justice coordinating council,

237
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:50,400
and from there,
something down in Washington

238
00:17:50,400 --> 00:17:54,700
with one of the police associations
- Six figures guaranteed.

239
00:17:55,700 --> 00:17:58,200
Go the right way, and attention will be paid.

240
00:17:58,200 --> 00:18:01,000
But you go kicking and screaming,
and no one -

241
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:04,000
not the caucus,
not the ministers, not me -

242
00:18:05,300 --> 00:18:07,300
will be there for you.

243
00:18:11,800 --> 00:18:13,800
