00:53:45,600 --> 00:53:48,700
I go after his people, you feel me?
You hurt enough of them,

737
00:53:48,800 --> 00:53:51,800
that snake gonna stick his head
above that hole.

738
00:53:51,900 --> 00:53:53,900
That one there, you know him?

739
00:53:54,000 --> 00:53:55,400
He's a lieutenant.

740
00:53:55,500 --> 00:53:58,000
We gonna go after him first.

741
00:53:58,100 --> 00:54:00,700
Mark that ride, yo.

742
00:54:01,200 --> 00:54:03,400
Oscar.

743
00:54:03,500 --> 00:54:05,500
- Lester.
- Thank you, baby.

744
00:54:05,500 --> 00:54:07,500
- Anytime, man.
- Yeah. All right.

745
00:54:14,700 --> 00:54:18,000
He's perfect. Can't be dead
more than a couple of hours.

746
00:54:18,000 --> 00:54:19,600
Better lose these.

747
00:54:28,000 --> 00:54:30,300
You're a twisted fuck, McNulty.

748
00:54:30,300 --> 00:54:33,300
Defense wounds. Help sell it.

749
00:54:33,400 --> 00:54:37,800
You got nerve calling me twisted.
You came up with the teeth.

750
00:54:37,800 --> 00:54:40,500
You know how these psycho
serial motherfuckers are.

751
00:54:40,500 --> 00:54:42,800
They mature.

752
00:54:42,800 --> 00:54:44,800
They start simple and crude

753
00:54:44,800 --> 00:54:48,700
and become more and more ornate.
There you go.

754
00:54:48,700 --> 00:54:51,400
Don't tell my mother or my priest
you saw me do this.

755
00:54:51,400 --> 00:54:52,900
Take it to my grave.

756
00:55:04,600 --> 00:55:07,500
- Want me to take that?
- Nah, I got it.

757
00:55:09,500 --> 00:55:12,800
What you see in this hole, man?
All the money you got?

758
00:55:15,000 --> 00:55:17,300
Your great-grandfather,

759
00:55:17,300 --> 00:55:20,600
first colored man to own his own house
in Johnson Square.

760
00:55:21,300 --> 00:55:25,500
That means something,
Something you young'uns lost.

761
00:55:26,700 --> 00:55:28,900
Yeah. Well, we outside
when you ready.

762
00:55:28,900 --> 00:55:32,700
Keep sharp while I'm gone, boy.
Charles say Omar back.

763
00:55:32,700 --> 00:55:34,500
He left Charles standing

764
00:55:34,500 --> 00:55:38,300
but he might feel less inclined
if he get the drop on you or yours.

765
00:55:38,400 --> 00:55:41,400
Ain't got to fret none about Omar.

766
00:55:47,900 --> 00:55:49,200
No need for that.

767
00:56:00,100 --> 00:56:02,400
You ain't come to see me off.

768
00:56:06,500 --> 00:56:07,700
My nephew.

769
00:56:12,200 --> 00:56:14,600
Boy was always a disappointment.

770
00:56:16,800 --> 00:56:19,000
But I treated you like a son.

771
00:56:19,100 --> 00:56:21,200
I wasn't made to play the son.

772
00:56:21,200 --> 00:56:23,100
But my supply - the good dope?

773
00:56:23,200 --> 00:56:25,900
The Greeks, they cool with it.

774
00:56:30,700 --> 00:56:34,000
Proposition, then -

775
00:56:34,000 --> 00:56:36,000
I just step out the way.

776
00:56:37,000 --> 00:56:39,900
You never hear from me again.
I just disappear.

777
00:56:40,000 --> 00:56:43,000
Joe, you'd be up into mischief in no time.

778
00:56:44,000 --> 00:56:47,900
Truth is, you wouldn't be able
to change up any more than me.

779
00:56:49,900 --> 00:56:51,400
Close your eyes.

780
00:56:54,300 --> 00:56:56,000
It won't hurt none.

781
00:56:58,300 --> 00:57:00,100
There, now.

782
00:57:01,900 --> 00:57:04,700
Joe, relax.

783
00:57:06,000 --> 00:57:07,700
Breathe easy.

